# pgCK OIDC auth-callout — per-deployment values.
# Real values live in an untracked `.env` (gitignored) or operator config — NEVER baked into
# source or committed docs. The realm public JWK + issuer + audience are DELIVERED BY CONFIG:
# no `.well-known` fetch, no egress HTTP in the live path (SPEC.OAUTH2 §3.3).

# --- Extension GUCs (set by the deployment/operator, e.g. postgresql.conf / ALTER SYSTEM) ---
# pgck.oidc_jwks     = {"keys":[…]}                       # realm JWKS; only Ed25519/OKP keys used
# pgck.oidc_issuer   = https://<keycloak-host>/realms/<realm>
# pgck.oidc_audience = account                            # the token `aud` (resource), not the client id (`azp`)

# --- Integration test: verifies_a_real_keycloak_token_from_env (#[ignore]) ---
# Supply these at run time from your dev realm (values not committed):
OIDC_TEST_ISS=https://<keycloak-host>/realms/<realm>
OIDC_TEST_AUD=account
# OIDC_TEST_JWKS  = "$(curl -s https://<keycloak-host>/realms/<realm>/protocol/openid-connect/certs)"
# OIDC_TEST_TOKEN = "$(… password grant …| jq -r .access_token)"
# OIDC_TEST_NOW   = "$(date +%s)"
